                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/12–2044: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-20">December 20,
                            1944</date>.<lb/>[Received December 20—4:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>865. Unofficial election figures through last night indicate Arévalo elected
                    President by wide margin of 261,432 against combined vote of about 40,000 for
                    other candidates of which Recinos obtained over 21,000.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
